sh literature, including canonical authors such as Shakespeare, Spenser, and Milton, as well as their female contemporaries such as Amelia Lanyer and Elizabeth Cary. It will also appeal to scholars of conduct literature; of early modern drama, popular literature, poetry, and prose; of women's history; and of gender theory"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on information from the publisher. 0aEnglish literatureyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aWomen and literaturezEnglandxHistory. 0aWomenzEnglandxConduct of life. 0aConduct of life in literature. 0aVirtue in literature. 0aSocial values in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 0aDidactic literature, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 4aElectronic books.2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)epublisher.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.7685052